  "prompt": "What will be my rank if I have scored 132/200 in MU-OET?",
  "response": "The MU-OET (Manipal University Online Entrance Test) is a competitive exam, and your rank will depend on the overall performance of all candidates. Since the test is scaled and normalized, your exact rank cannot be determined solely based on your raw score of 132/200. However, you can estimate your rank based on the following:\n\n1. **Previous Year Trends:** Look at previous years' cutoff scores and ranks to get an idea of where your score might place you. If 132 is significantly above the previous cutoff, you may have a good rank.\n\n2. **Percentile:** If the exam results provide a percentile, it can help you understand how you performed relative to others. A higher percentile (e.g., 90th percentile or above) typically indicates a better rank.\n\n3. **Competition:** The number of candidates and their performance this year will also influence your rank. If the competition is tougher, your rank may be lower even with a decent score.\n\n4. **Official Rank List:** For the most accurate rank, you\u2019ll need to wait for the official rank list or merit list released by the university.\n\nTo get a better estimate, you can consult with your coaching institute (if applicable) or check forums where candidates discuss their scores and ranks. However, the official result will provide the most accurate information.",
